snippet.title: Academia.edu acquires Plasmyd to let peers review papers
snippet.description: The online repository of academic research papers is building in a new variant of the ages-old peer-review process to scrutinize academic work.

snippet.title: Fujifilm X-T1
snippet.description: The Fujifilm X-T1 is a great camera for advanced photographers as long as its quirks don't bother you.

snippet.title: Thief (PlayStation 4)
snippet.description: Suffering from boring, uninspired gameplay, Thief is nearly dead on arrival. Plain and simple, it's just not fun to play.

snippet.title: Papers shed light on shutdown of 'Snowden' e-mail provider
snippet.description: Newly unsealed court papers reveal the circumstances behind the sudden closure of the encrypted e-mail service said to have been used by NSA leaker Edward Snowden.

snippet.title: Twitter reportedly filed its IPO papers with SEC in July
snippet.description: Social network managed to keep its IPO papers under wraps for nearly two months under provisions of the JOBS Act, sources tell AllThingsD's Kara Swisher.

snippet.title: How to get the best photos from Android 4.4 KitKat
snippet.description: Android 4.4 KitKat comes with a new camera app and there are some neat new features that you should make yourself aware of.

snippet.title: Groupon files its IPO papers
snippet.description: The company that pioneered the daily-deals business is seeking $750 million in the offering, following the recent IPO from LinkedIn.

snippet.title: Logitech Ultrathin Keyboard Mini
snippet.description: The Logitech Ultrathin Keyboard Mini is arguably the best keyboard/case option available for the iPad Mini, but it still doesn't offer a great typing experience.

snippet.title: Facebook isn't the place to serve legal papers, says judge
snippet.description: A federal judges rules that Chase Bank can't serve an alleged identity thief with papers on Facebook. Offering a strange glimmer of hope to the newspaper business, he suggests a local paper might be a better place.
